arrayOf("Basoya / Baisoya / Besoya","बसोया / बैसोया / बीसोया (बैसौया)","According to Gurjar Bhaat (Brahmins who keep records of family Generation of Gurjars). In 972 AD when Gurjar Saroha king Karna Singh was ruling; they migrated to Ghazni city of Afghanistan and fought with a Muslim king there. In that war they killed son of that king and to avoid further clash with the king they headed back to Bharat (ancient India). On their way to Bharat (Ancient India); they slept in a field of cotton (Bai) (In Gujari : Bai Soye). This Bai soye distorted to Baisoya with time. \n\nBaisoya surname is mostly in pillanji village","Devasya baisoya"),
